  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And they brought them into this retention tank.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Otto Friedrich was apparently notified by the Polish police of the find, that they had a group of gypsy children in the retention tank.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "He-- he-- he ordered the Polish policemen to open the tank.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And the children were attracted by the motorcycle and the light, and so they start-- they came running at-- at Otto Friedrich.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "He-- he calmly took out his revolver.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "It was a shiny one.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "He shot one after another in the head.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And with his boots, he made a heap, a neat heap, of all the eight children.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "He killed one after another.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "They-- the-- the big ones came first, so they were killed first.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "The little ones didn't even understand.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "They thought it's firecrackers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "When it was all over, he called the Polish policeman, made him shine his boots, the ones that he used to make a neat heap out of the children, and to clean the backyard.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "He drove off on the motorcycle as if nothing happened.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That was a story of Otto Friedrich.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "[SIGHS] This is one of the stories that I witnessed, simply because I was by the window looking down at the courtyard.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Until the outbreak of the war between Germany and the Soviet Union, I don't remember having seen any overt killing or murder in the streets.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I have seen demeaning brutality, disrespect, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] every kind of chicanery you can think of, but not killing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The killing started with the moment the Germans apparently got rid of Soviet intervention.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Once the Soviet Union was attacked-- I'm talking about June 22, 1941-- the killing started [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to show itself, obviously, openly, in the streets.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
